FBIS3-13795 "drnes054_s_94007" FBIS-NES-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Mar 1994 Iran CIA Reportedly Funding Secular Press in Turkey LD1903162494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1530 GMT 19 Mar 94 LD1903162494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Text] America's intelligence and spying agency, the CIA, in order to encourage the press to increase their propaganda attacks on Islam, has provided $35 million of financial aid to the writers of the secular press in Turkey. (BIKEK) newspaper, published in Istanbul, carries this report in today's edition, adding that, by making use of the CIA's financial assistance and the support of Western countries, Turkey's secular newspapers have started an extensive propaganda campaign among Turkey's secular circles against the Islamic-leaning Rafah [Prosperity] party.
